description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Trust Registrar to join the Cardiology Service at Hinchingbrooke Hospital, as part of North West Anglia NHS Foundation Trust. It is an exciting time to join our Trust as we are proactively working on the development of our Cardiology Services. The successful candidate will be eager to work in a busy and diverse service working closely with other specialties and have the opportunity of shaping the service as we actively work on moving them forwards this year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in the busy town of Huntingdon, Hinchingbrooke Hospital has a lively and vibrant working atmosphere, with quick and easy transport links. The size of our Trust enable us to offer a range of attractive benefits and resources as well as great education and development opportunities for staff at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NWAFT prides itself on its investment in staff both in terms of developing career skills as well as its commitment to staff health and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current set-up of the Cardiology Service at Hinchingbrooke Hospital is with outpatient clinics and an inpatient in-reach service across different wards. We are moving towards having a specialist Cardiology bed-base and the successful candidate would be part of this working group to realise our ambition and move our Cardiology Service forwards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full details about the role and service are available in the information pack in this job advert. We would strongly recommend that anyone interested in the role gets in touch for an informal discussion or to arrange a visit. Please contact one of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Dunkerley&lt;br /&gt;Assistant General Manager&lt;br /&gt;Cardiology &amp; Respiratory&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rebecca.Dunkerley@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;07885 479 808&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Jo Porter&lt;br /&gt;Clinical Lead, Cardiology&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jo.Porter1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
